      <hedline>
        <hl1>A MISSING MUSEUM?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Leslie Pollack letter on David Allan's May 20 travel article on Baltimore, Md, says it failed to mention American Visionary Art Museum</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: How David Allan in ''36 Hours: Baltimore'' (May 20) can use the phrases ''galleries that specialize in contemporary art'' and ''alternative arts in Baltimore'' and not direct visitors to the American Visionary Art Museum is puzzling indeed. Situated on Key Highway, on the south side of Baltimore's Inner Harbor, the museum has fabulous outsider art. Stop by the Visitor Center on the harbor and ask my 81-year-old father to point you in the right direction. If he's not working, someone else will help you.</p>
        <p>Leslie Pollack  Bethany, Conn.</p>
      </block>
